Mauritian rupee steady vs the dollar and stg . The Mauritian rupee was steady against both dollar and sterling on Wednesday reflecting international market trends , foreign exchange dealers said . The rupee was fixed at a commercial mean rate of 20 . 6295 to the dollar from 20 . 6165 on Tuesday , and at a commercial mean rate of 33 . 742 to the sterling from 33 . 732 on Tuesday . Forex dealers said the dollar ' s strengthening was due to the left - wing victory in French parliamentary elections on Sunday . They added that United States jobs data would be published on Friday and the dollar ' s fixing on international markets could be influenced positively or negatively by these figures . Forex dealers said that some commercial banks were showing sign of hard currency shortage positions . - - Clifford Vellien + + 230 211 - 9555 . 
